\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Hmm, the sessions_list returns empty. But wait - this cron session itself must be running somewhere. The cron system must be using a session for this. Let me look at the cron delivery mode.\\n\\nThe cron for `ed2d0b5d` has `sessionTarget: \\\"isolated\\\"` and `delivery.mode: \\\"announce\\\"` with `channel: \\\"telegram\\\"` and `to: \\\"-5163901258\\\"`. This means when the cron finishes, it delivers to Telegram. But I'm in the middle of execution right now.\\n\\nLooking at the system more carefully - the delivery is handled by the cron runner at completion. Since I was spawned as an isolated agent by the cron, the delivery should happen automatically when I finish. \\n\\nSo I just need to produce the final report as my reply. The cron runner will take whatever text I output and send it to the Telegram group. Let me verify the cron job has the right delivery configuration - it does, so my plain text response will be automatically delivered.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"\\n**Pipeline: DEGRADED** — the delivery is configured to announce to group -5163901258 upon cron completion. Returning the report now:\\n\\n---\\n\\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | 04:52 UTC 15 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status to Lead) — entered **ERROR** state; 6 consecutive timeout errors\\n• All 3 prior cron sessions cleared from sessions_list (expected: isolated ephemeral sessions)\\n• `cron:e7885813` lastRunStatus: **error** | lastErrorReason: timeout\\n\\nPipeline: **DEGRADED**\\n• Active sessions: 0 (ephemeral — cleaned after run)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: `e7885813` — Agent Status to Lead (6x timeout, needs review/kill)\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 133,\n            \"output\": 409,\n            \"totalTokens\": 18656,\n            \"cacheRead\": 17253,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 861,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776228765774,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e4c9eaa70c29963cd67954763abdf\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"4ff54d92\",\n            \"seq\": 13\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"telegram\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-telegram-direct-6053576134\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"telegram:6053576134\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776228279119,\n      \"sessionId\": \"8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 142476,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776228252091,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776228276189,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 24098,\n      \"childSessions\": [\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8d8e1952-016d-4c2d-819c-c3b32e3b45b2\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8bffa95f-1686-4571-a0ed-e69d265eb964\"\n      ],\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:6053576134\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"main_bot\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The Lead is asking if after cloning, installing, and running the setup, they can delete the entire setup folder. The answer is: mostly yes, but they should keep the skills.pack if they want to re-run setup, and they should keep the bin/ahv-setup.js if they want to re-run. But actually, after setup completes, everything is installed into ~/.openclaw/ and the setup repo is no longer needed. The user can delete the repo folder after setup.\\n\\nHowever, the skills.pack gets unpacked into ~/.openclaw/ so after setup runs, the skills are already in place.\\n\\nSo yes, Lead can delete the setup folder after setup completes successfully.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Đúng rồi Lead! Sau khi chạy xong thành công:\\n\\n- ✅ Config đã nằm ở `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\\n- ✅ Skills đã giải mã vào `~/.openclaw/workspaces/{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`\\n- ✅ `skills.pack` đã unpack xong\\n\\n**Xóa thoải mái** — repo setup không còn cần nữa.\\n\\nChỉ giữ lại nếu muốn **chạy lại setup** (ví dụ: đổi team, reset config).\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 184,\n            \"output\": 280,\n            \"totalTokens\": 141970,\n            \"cacheRead\": 141261,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 245,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestam